The paper focuses on developing a method for providing real-time feedback in simulation-based learning (SBL), which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed method utilizes neural networks, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed method, which could be relevant to the subfields of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
